==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Geniculate
<hw>Ge*nic"u*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>geniculatus</ets>, fr. <ets>geniculum</ets> little knee, knot or
joint, dim. of <ets>genu</ets> knee. See <er>Knee</er>.]</ety> <def>Bent
abruptly at an angle, like the knee when bent; <as>as, a
<ex>geniculate</ex> stem; a <ex>geniculate</ex> ganglion; a
<ex>geniculate</ex> twin crystal.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Geniculate</ent>⟦br⟧

